 Google Hangouts
 *https://hangouts.google.com/call/ys7zseukwgocc4tqkr5i7yaav4b
 
 Proper build ID for today: 20151016 or 20151015
 
 Simulator
 If you need to set up the simulator, please look here: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/WebIDE 
 Also get the most recent xpi (gets you the most recent version of Firefox OS 2.5 simulator build)
 Linux: https://queue.taskcluster.net/v1/task/KZB71dAOQ6-49CAx2XEVaw/artifacts/public/build/fxos-simulator.xpi
 Windows: You have to use mullet builds for now - http://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/mozilla.org/b2g/nightly/latest-mozilla-central/b2g-44.0a1.en-US.win32.zip

     -download and unzip file into one folder and run the b2g.exe to start the mullet b2g

mac: you also have to use mullet for mac right now also http://ftp.mozilla.org/pub/mozilla.org/b2g/nightly/latest-mozilla-central/b2g-44.0a1.en-US.mac64.dmg
            -download the .dmg and unpack it and run the one that is called b2g it should open the mulet that you can use to test firefox os
            
Flame reference Device
For testing device, if you dont have v18D_nightly_v4 on you device you will need to full flash your device then shallow flash
Full flashing: https://oneanddone.mozilla.org/en-US/tasks/141/
Shallow flashing: https://oneanddone.mozilla.org/en-US/tasks/146/
 
Filing Bugs

    If you file a bug, please set the whiteboard to [fxos testday]. Also, it would be great if you could add your name and the bugs you worked on in this etherpad so that we can acknowledge your contributions. Thanks! 

    You can use this guide to help you file Firefox OS bugs: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Mozilla/Firefox_OS/Developing_Firefox_OS/Filing_bugs_against_Firefox_OS

    If you find a bug that was already found for this test day, please comment in the bug that you were able to reproduce it.

    List of bugs found during the test day:


https://bugzilla.mozilla.org/buglist.cgi?list_id=12616889&status_whiteboard_type=allwordssubstr&status_whiteboard=[fxos%20testday]&resolution=---&query_format=advanced

Most of the tests you will be running are on One and Done: https://oneanddone.mozilla.org/en-US/?search=&team=4 - with the exception of BuddyUp Testing below:

BuddyUp Notification Testing

    Follow the instructions on Line 10 of this etherpad -> https://public.etherpad-mozilla.org/p/BuddyUpTestPlan

    Make sure to create an account so you can answer questions - http://mailinator.com/ is a great site for throwaway email addresses

    Ask and answer a series of questions and confirm you get a notification in the following cases:

    When someone adds a comment to your thread

    When a solution is offered to the question you asked

    Spot check the following locales:

    English, Spanish, Portuguese


You can test the entire Firefox OS if you feel so inclined, these are just some tasks to get people started!

Also when you decide you are done testing for the event, please stop by and fill out a survey so we can work to improve the Firefox OS test days: http://www.surveygizmo.com/s3/2382230/FXOS-Test-Day-Feedback

